cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD

The paper presents a novel complex gated recurrent cell for RNNs, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for processing time series and sequence information. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also applies the technique to human motion prediction, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SD (Sound).
